    <para><emphasis role="bold">Description:</emphasis> A string added to the beginning of every log message. It can be used to add an arbitrary string to any log source, though it is most commonly used for adding <userinput>kernel:</userinput> to the kernel messages on Linux. NOTE: This option is deprecated. Use <parameter>program-override()</parameter> instead.</para>
